Both deliverables emitted in the working directory:

- `transcript.json` — 20 iterations, 52 hypotheses, 51 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`. Top-level `dataset_id`, `model_id`, `harness_id`, `max_iterations=25` set.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative walk-through of stages 1–5 plus a supported/refuted hypothesis ledger.

Headline findings:
- Strongest predictors of `objective_response` (n=50,000, baseline rate 16.9%): negative — `feature_013` (logOR -0.30), `feature_067` (-0.25), `feature_011` continuous (-0.04 per unit); positive — `feature_006` (+0.13), `feature_092` (+0.16), `feature_099` (+0.09).
- Race, smoking, histology, insurance, and age-like `feature_078` are NOT independently associated after biomarker adjustment.
- Effects are largely additive; two robust synergies: `feature_006 × feature_007` (p=0.004) and `feature_092 × feature_013` (p=0.037, effect concentrated in `feature_013`=1).
- Adjusted model AUC ≈ 0.572; top-decile predicted response ~24% vs bottom-decile ~11%.
